## Container productivity

The association between *Aedes aegypti* pupal abundance and household water storage practices was evaluated using a generalized linear mixed model (GLMM) with a Poisson distribution and log link function, including random intercepts for household (CV) and surveyor to account for repeated measurements and potential observer effects.

```{r}
ContMod1 <- gamm4(TotPupa_AE ~ Season + Year + Community
                  + ProbAgua 
                  + TotBarAgua  
                  + TotPilaAgua 
                  + TotLlanAgua
                  + TotBaldeAgua, 
                  family = poisson,
                  random = ~(1|CV) + (1|Encuestador),
                  data = df3)

summary(ContMod1$gam)
summary(ContMod1$mer)

check_autocorrelation(ContMod1$gam)

plot(check_collinearity(ContMod1$gam))

tab <- tidy(
